'''Nuno Alexandre Pereira Mendes''' (born 7 April 1978) is a [[Portugal|Portuguese]] [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Gondomar S.C.|Gondomar]].

He began his career with [[Vit<U+00F3>ria S.C.|Vit<U+00F3>ria Guimar<U+00E3>es]] and made his [[first team]] debut during the 1996<U+2013>97 [[Primeira Liga]] season. Mendes spent three seasons in [[Liga de Honra]], playing for [[C.D. Aves|Aves]], [[F.C. Felgueiras|Felgueiras]] and [[G.D. Chaves|Chaves]] respectively before moving to France to join [[Ligue 1|Division 1]] club [[RC Strasbourg|Strasbourg]] in 2000. He returned to Portugal a year later to play for [[U.D. Leiria|Uni<U+00E3>o Leiria]], managed by [[Jos<U+00E9> Mourinho]], before spending a brief period with [[S.C. Braga|Braga]] in 2002. He spent 18 months with [[Moreirense F.C.|Moreirense]] and then dropped down a division to play for [[C.D. Santa Clara|Santa Clara]] in 2004.

A year later, Mendes played in England for [[Football League Championship|Championship]] club [[Plymouth Argyle F.C.|Plymouth Argyle]] before returning to France with [[US Cr<U+00E9>teil-Lusitanos|Cr<U+00E9>teil]] of [[Ligue 2]]. Having spent a brief spell with [[F.C. Penafiel|Penafiel]] in 2007, he returned to Aves, where he played for two seasons in Liga de Honra. He dropped down to the Portuguese [[Portuguese Second Division|third division]] in 2009 to play for Moreirense before spending a season with [[C.D. Trofense|Trofense]]. In 2010, he joined third division side [[Gondomar S.C.|Gondomar]].

==Club career==
Mendes was born in [[Guimar<U+00E3>es]].<ref name="ZeroZero">[http://www.zerozerofootball.com/player/nuno_mendes/current/profile/0/default/258/ "Nuno Mendes"]. ZeroZeroFootball. Retrieved 5 February 2011.</ref> He joined his home town club, [[Vit<U+00F3>ria S.C.|Vit<U+00F3>ria Guimar<U+00E3>es]], at an early age and progressed through their youth system.<ref>[http://www.record.xl.pt/arquivo/interior.aspx?content_id=109198 "Les<U+00E3>o afasta Nuno Mendes"] (in Portuguese). ''[[Record (newspaper)|Record]]''. 4 January 2002. Retrieved 5 February 2011.</ref> He made his [[first team]] debut in a 4<U+2013>1 win against [[G.D. Chaves|Chaves]] on 23 February 1997.<ref>[http://www.zerozerofootball.com/jogo.php?id=14717 "V. Guimar<U+00E3>es 4<U+2013>1 Chaves"]. ZeroZeroFootball. Retrieved 5 February 2011.</ref> He made 5 more appearances [[1996<U+2013>97 Primeira Liga|that season]], including a 1<U+2013>0 defeat to [[C.S. Mar<U+00ED>timo|Mar<U+00ED>timo]] on 2 May 1997,<ref>[http://www.zerozerofootball.com/jogo.php?id=14715 "V. Guimar<U+00E3>es 0<U+2013>1 Mar<U+00ED>timo"]. ZeroZeroFootball. Retrieved 5 February 2011.</ref> which was his last for Vit<U+00F3>ria.<ref name="L'<U+00C9>quipe"/> Mendes joined [[Liga de Honra]] side [[C.D. Aves|Aves]] on [[Loan (association football)|loan]] for the 1997<U+2013>98 season.<ref name="Moreirense/loan moves">[http://www.record.xl.pt/arquivo/interior.aspx?content_id=148689 "Nuno Mendes confirmado"] (in Portuguese). ''[[Record (newspaper)|Record]]''. 18 January 2003. Retrieved 5 February 2011.</ref> He scored four goals in 27 league appearances for the club as they finished 15th in the table.<ref>[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesp/port98.html "Portugal 1997/98"]. [[Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation]]. 6 August 2001. Retrieved 21 March 2011.</ref> The following season, he joined [[F.C. Felgueiras|Felgueiras]] on loan.<ref name="Moreirense/loan moves"/> They finished 5th in Liga de Honra and Mendes was a first team regular.<ref>[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesp/port99.html "Portugal 1998/99"]. [[Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation]]. Alcino Pascoal. 6 August 2001. Retrieved 21 March 2011.</ref> He made 28 league appearances and scored two goals.{{ref label|Felgueiras|A|}} Mendes had his [[Association football contracts|contract]] with Vit<U+00F3>ria Guimar<U+00E3>es terminated in June 1999, allowing him to sign a two-year deal with Chaves.<ref>[http://www.record.xl.pt/arquivo/interior.aspx?content_id=6596 "Nuno Mendes refor<U+00E7>a defesa do D. Chaves"] (in Portuguese). ''[[Record (newspaper)|Record]]''. 29 June 1999. Retrieved 6 February 2011.</ref>

He made 27 league appearances in his only season with the club, scoring twice,<ref name="Futebol365">[http://www.futebol365.pt/jogadores/info_jogador.asp?id=11548 "Nuno Mendes"] (in Portuguese). Futebol365. Retrieved 5 February 2011.</ref> as they finished 12th in Liga de Honra.<ref>[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesp/port00.html "Portugal 1999/2000"]. [[Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation]]. Alcino Pascoal. 13 August 2001. Retrieved 21 March 2011.</ref> He moved to France in June 2000 to play for [[Ligue 1|Division 1]] club [[RC Strasbourg|Strasbourg]].<ref>[http://www.record.xl.pt/arquivo/interior.aspx?content_id=35351 "Estrasburgo contrata Nuno Mendes ao Desp. Chaves"] (in Portuguese). ''[[Record (newspaper)|Record]]''. 9 June 2000. Retrieved 6 February 2011.</ref> Having signed a four-year contract,<ref>[http://www.record.xl.pt/arquivo/interior.aspx?content_id=35293 "Nuno Mendes vai para o Estrasburgo"] (in Portuguese). ''[[Record (newspaper)|Record]]''. 9 June 2000. Retrieved 6 February 2011.</ref> he made his debut in a 1<U+2013>1 draw at [[Lille OSC|Lille]] on 29 November 2000.<ref>[http://www.lfp.fr/ligue1/feuille_match/45816 "LOSC Lille M<U+00E9>tropole 1<U+2013>1 RC Strasbourg"] (in French). [[Ligue de Football Professionnel]]. Retrieved 6 February 2011.</ref> He found first team opportunities limited during the [[2000<U+2013>01 Division 1|2000<U+2013>01 season]], making six more league appearances as the club were relegated to [[Ligue 2|Division 2]].<ref>[http://www.lfp.fr/ligue1/classement?saison=78#sai=69&journee1=1&journee2=34&cat=Gen "2000/2001 classements"] (in French). [[Ligue de Football Professionnel]]. Retrieved 6 February 2011.</ref>{{ref label|LFP|B|}} However, the season did end well for Mendes as he won his first trophy as a professional, the [[Coupe de France]].<ref>[http://www.fff.fr/competitions/php/histo_cfra/histo_cfra.php?sa_no=2001&pj_no=6 "Coupe de France: Saison 2000<U+2013>2001"] (in French). [[French Football Federation]]. Retrieved 6 February 2011.</ref> He made two appearances in the competition, but did not play in the [[2001 Coupe de France Final|final]] where Strasbourg defeated [[Amiens SC|Amiens]] on [[Penalty shootout|penalties]].<ref>[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesf/fran01.html "France 2000/01"]. [[Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation]]. Fr<U+00E9>d<U+00E9>ric Pauron and Karel Stokkermans. 6 October 2001. Retrieved 21 March 2011.</ref><ref>[http://www.record.xl.pt/arquivo/interior.aspx?content_id=85982 "Nuno Mendes: Ganhar Ta<U+00E7>a de Fran<U+00E7>a j<U+00E1> pesa no curr<U+00ED>culo"] (in Portuguese). ''[[Record (newspaper)|Record]]''. 29 May 2001. Retrieved 6 February 2011.</ref>

Mendes returned to Portugal ahead of the [[2001<U+2013>02 Primeira Liga|2001<U+2013>02 season]], joining [[Primeira Liga]] club [[U.D. Leiria|Uni<U+00E3>o Leiria]] on a season-long loan.<ref>[http://www.record.xl.pt/arquivo/interior.aspx?content_id=82558 "Nuno Mendes refor<U+00E7>a equipa na pr<U+00F3>xima temporada"] (in Portuguese). ''[[Record (newspaper)|Record]]''. 8 May 2001. Retrieved 6 February 2011.</ref> Reflecting on his time in France, he said "I never hid my desire to return to Portugal, but now I can not say anything more."<ref>[http://www.record.xl.pt/arquivo/interior.aspx?content_id=82594 "Nuno Mendes refor<U+00E7>a leirienses"] (in Portuguese). ''[[Record (newspaper)|Record]]''. 9 May 2001. Retrieved 6 February 2011.</ref> He made his debut on 11 August 2001 in a 0<U+2013>0 draw at [[S.C. Braga|Braga]].<ref>[http://www.zerozerofootball.com/jogo.php?id=17770 "Sp. Braga 0<U+2013>0 U. Leiria"]. ZeroZeroFootball. Retrieved 21 March 2011.</ref> Mendes played regularly under the management of [[Jos<U+00E9> Mourinho]] prior to his departure to [[F.C. Porto|Porto]],<ref name="Leaving Leiria">[http://www.record.xl.pt/arquivo/interior.aspx?content_id=121322 "Nuno Mendes abandona equipa"] (in Portuguese). ''[[Record (newspaper)|Record]]''. 25 April 2002. Retrieved 6 February 2011.</ref> but fell out of favour under his replacement, [[V<U+00ED>tor Pontes]]. He made 16 league appearances for Leiria, helping the club finish 7th in the Primeira Liga,<ref name="L'<U+00C9>quipe"/><ref>[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesp/port02.html "Portugal 2001/02"]. [[Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation]]. Alcino Pascoal, Jos<U+00E9> Batalha, Dalencia Garcia and Jan Schoenmakers. 12 September 2002. Retrieved 21 March 2011.</ref> before returning to Strasbourg.<ref name="Leaving Leiria"/> Upon his departure, Mendes was critical of the club's president Jo<U+00E3>o Bartolomeu, who he believed created instability at the club. "The Union of Leiria is a complicated club at senior management level, especially the president, who sees things where they do not exist and it creates instability in the squad," said Mendes who "leaves great friends in Leiria".<ref>[http://www.record.xl.pt/arquivo/interior.aspx?content_id=121811 "Nuno Mendes critica presidente na hora do abandono"] (in Portuguese). ''[[Record (newspaper)|Record]]''. 29 April 2002. Retrieved 6 February 2011.</ref>

In May 2002, he signed a two-year contract with Braga.<ref>[http://www.record.xl.pt/arquivo/interior.aspx?content_id=122352 "Telmo e Nuno Mendes juntam-se a Wender"] (in Portuguese). ''[[Record (newspaper)|Record]]''. 4 May 2002. Retrieved 6 February 2011.</ref><ref>[http://www.record.xl.pt/arquivo/interior.aspx?content_id=122771 "Nuno Mendes assina hoje... Arthur ser<U+00E1> o pr<U+00F3>ximo"] (in Portuguese). ''[[Record (newspaper)|Record]]''. 8 May 2002. Retrieved 6 February 2011.</ref> He made his debut in a 3<U+2013>2 defeat at [[C.F. Os Belenenses|Belenenses]] on 5 October 2002.<ref>[http://www.zerozerofootball.com/jogo.php?id=46 "Belenenses 3<U+2013>2 Sp. Braga"]. ZeroZeroFootball. Retrieved 6 February 2011.</ref> In a season disrupted by injuries,<ref>[http://www.record.xl.pt/arquivo/interior.aspx?content_id=143408 "Nuno Mendes apto a retomar treino de grupo"] (in Portuguese). ''[[Record (newspaper)|Record]]''. 26 November 2002. Retrieved 6 February 2011.</ref> Mendes only played in one more match for Braga, against his old club Vit<U+00F3>ria Guimar<U+00E3>es.<ref name="ZeroZero"/>{{ref label|Braga|C|}} He had his contract cancelled in January 2003,<ref>[http://www.record.xl.pt/arquivo/interior.aspx?content_id=148341 "Nuno Mendes por horas"] (in Portuguese). ''[[Record (newspaper)|Record]]''. 15 January 2003. Retrieved 6 February 2011.</ref> which allowed him to join [[Moreirense F.C.|Moreirense]].<ref name="Moreirense/loan moves"/> He made his debut on 3 February 2003 in a 1<U+2013>1 draw at [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]].<ref>[http://www.zerozerofootball.com/jogo.php?id=173 "Benfica 1<U+2013>1 Moreirense"]. ZeroZeroFootball. Retrieved 6 February 2011.</ref> He made two more appearances [[2002<U+2013>03 Primeira Liga|that season]] as the club finished 12th in the table. Having fractured his foot in July 2003,<ref>[http://www.record.xl.pt/arquivo/interior.aspx?content_id=168583 "Nuno Mendes obrigado a parar"] (in Portuguese). ''[[Record (newspaper)|Record]]''. 26 July 2003. Retrieved 6 February 2011.</ref> he was used sparingly during the [[2003<U+2013>04 Primeira Liga|2003<U+2013>04 season]] by manager [[Manuel Machado (football manager)|Manuel Machado]]. He made four league appearances in an injury-plagued season,<ref name="L'<U+00C9>quipe"/><ref>[http://www.record.xl.pt/arquivo/interior.aspx?content_id=192378 "Nuno Mendes reavaliado"] (in Portuguese). ''[[Record (newspaper)|Record]]''. 30 March 2004. Retrieved 6 February 2011.</ref> as the club finished 9th in the Primeira Liga. Mendes dropped down a division in June 2004 after signing a one-year contract with [[C.D. Santa Clara|Santa Clara]].<ref name="Santa Clara signing">[http://www.record.xl.pt/arquivo/interior.aspx?content_id=201891 "Nuno Mendes assina por uma temporada"] (in Portuguese). ''[[Record (newspaper)|Record]]''. 26 June 2004. Retrieved 6 February 2011.</ref> "This project is attractive," he said. "The coach, Jose Morais, spoke to me and showed willingness in me to go to the [[Azores]] and that's important. I know that Santa Clara is going through some difficulties, but the Department intends to make a financial recovery in time and maybe next season bet on rising."<ref name="Santa Clara signing"/>

He made his debut on 29 August 2004 in a 3<U+2013>1 defeat against [[C.D. Feirense|Feirense]] and was sent off for two bookable offences.<ref>[http://www.lpfp.pt/liga_orangina/pages/jogo.aspx?epoca=20042005&jornada=1&jogo=311 "Sta. Clara 1<U+2013>3 Feirense"] (in Portuguese). [[Portuguese League for Professional Football]]. Retrieved 7 February 2011.</ref> The club finished 15th in Liga de Honra in the 2004<U+2013>05 season,<ref>[http://www.lpfp.pt/liga_orangina/pages/classificacao_resultados.aspx?epoca=20042005 "2004<U+2013>2005: Classifica<U+00E7><U+00E3>o detalhada (Jornada n<U+00BA> 34)"] (in Portuguese). [[Portuguese League for Professional Football]]. Retrieved 7 February 2011.</ref> with Mendes making 17 league appearances.{{ref label|Santa Clara|D|}} He scored his first goal for the club in his final game, a 4<U+2013>0 win against [[Associa<U+00E7><U+00E3>o Naval 1<U+00BA> de Maio|Naval]] on 22 May 2005.<ref>[http://www.lpfp.pt/liga_orangina/pages/jogo.aspx?epoca=20042005&jornada=34&jogo=604 "Sta. Clara 4<U+2013>0 Naval"] (in Portuguese). [[Portuguese League for Professional Football]]. Retrieved 7 February 2011.</ref> After his contract with Santa Clara expired, he joined English [[Football League Championship|Championship]] club [[Plymouth Argyle F.C.|Plymouth Argyle]] on their pre-season tour of [[Sweden]] in July 2005.<ref>[http://www.greensonscreen.co.uk/sv-tour-sweden05.asp "Sweden 2005"]. Greens on Screen. Retrieved 7 February 2011.</ref> Having appeared in friendlies against [[Betsele IF|Betsele]] and [[Ume<U+00E5> FC|Ume<U+00E5>]], he signed a permanent contract with the club.<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/p/plymouth_argyle/4696719.stm "Mendes becomes sixth new signing"]. [[BBC Sport]]. 19 July 2005. Retrieved 7 February 2011.</ref><ref>[http://www.greensonscreen.co.uk/gosdb-players2.asp?pid=571&scp=1,2,3,4,5,6,7 "Nuno Mendes"]. Greens on Screen. Retrieved 9 February 2011.</ref> "I am delighted to have got him," said manager [[Bobby Williamson]] of his new signing. "It's a great opportunity that I could not miss," Mendes said in an interview with Portuguese newspaper ''[[Record (newspaper)|Record]]''. "It is valid for two seasons, with a few perks that are unheard of in Portugal. Essentially, the level of premiums for targets, as is normal in English football."<ref>[http://www.record.xl.pt/arquivo/interior.aspx?content_id=244008 "Nuno Mendes assinou finalmente pelo Plymouth"] (in Portuguese). ''[[Record (newspaper)|Record]]''. 20 July 2005. Retrieved 7 February 2011.</ref> 

Mendes made his debut in a 1<U+2013>0 defeat at [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]] on 20 August 2005.<ref>[http://www.pafc.co.uk/page/MatchReport/0,,10364~29660,00.html "Crystal Palace 1<U+2013>0 Plymouth"]. [[Plymouth Argyle F.C.|Plymouth Argyle]]. 20 August 2005. Retrieved 7 February 2011.</ref> He made two more appearances, including one in a 2<U+2013>1 [[Football League Cup|League Cup]] win against [[Peterborough United F.C.|Peterborough United]],<ref>[http://www.pafc.co.uk/page/MatchReport/0,,10364~31432,00.html "Plymouth 2<U+2013>1 Peterborough"]. [[Plymouth Argyle F.C.|Plymouth Argyle]]. 23 August 2005. Retrieved 7 February 2011.</ref> before losing his place in the squad when Bobby Williamson was replaced by [[Tony Pulis]] as manager.<ref name="PAFC"/><ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/p/plymouth_argyle/4272258.stm "Pulis confirmed as Plymouth boss"]. [[BBC Sport]]. 23 September 2005. Retrieved 7 February 2011.</ref> He had a trial with [[Major League Soccer]] club [[New York Red Bulls|New York Metrostars]] in January 2006 before his contract with Plymouth Argyle was cancelled by mutual consent.<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/p/plymouth_argyle/4665492.stm "Mendes completes Argyle departure"]. [[BBC Sport]]. 31 January 2006. Retrieved 7 February 2011.</ref> In June 2006, he returned to France where he signed a two-year contract with [[US Cr<U+00E9>teil-Lusitanos|Cr<U+00E9>teil]] of [[Ligue 2]].<ref>[http://www.ligue1.com/ligue2/article/nuno-mendes-a-creteil.htm "Nuno Mendes <U+00E0> Cr<U+00E9>teil"] (in French). [[Ligue de Football Professionnel]]. 28 June 2006. Retrieved 7 February 2011.</ref><ref>[http://www.foot-national.com/flashes-1606.html "Nuno Mendes a sign<U+00E9>"] (in French). Foot National. 27 June 2006. Retrieved 7 February 2011.</ref> He made his debut on 28 July 2006 in a 0<U+2013>0 draw with [[En Avant de Guingamp|Guingamp]].<ref>[http://www.ligue1.com/ligue2/feuille_match/50909 "US Cr<U+00E9>teil 0<U+2013>0 EA Guingamp"]. [[Ligue de Football Professionnel]]. Retrieved 7 February 2011.</ref> Mendes made six more appearances for the club,<ref name="LFP Cr<U+00E9>teil"/> before being released from his contract in December 2006.<ref>[http://www.ligue1.com/ligue2/article/nuno-mendes-quitte-creteil.htm "Nuno Mendes quitte Cr<U+00E9>teil"] (in French). [[Ligue de Football Professionnel]]. 12 December 2006. Retrieved 7 February 2011.</ref> A month later, he returned to Portugal where he signed a short-term contract with Liga de Honra club [[F.C. Penafiel|Penafiel]].<ref>[http://www.record.xl.pt/arquivo/interior.aspx?content_id=294339 "Nuno Mendes est<U+00E1> por horas"] (in Portuguese). ''[[Record (newspaper)|Record]]''. 18 January 2007. Retrieved 7 February 2011.</ref> He made his debut in a 1<U+2013>0 defeat at [[Rio Ave F.C.|Rio Ave]] on 4 February 2007,<ref>[http://www.lpfp.pt/liga_orangina/pages/jogo.aspx?epoca=20062007&jornada=17&jogo=3950 "Rio Ave 1<U+2013>0 Penafiel"] (in Portuguese). [[Portuguese League for Professional Football]]. Retrieved 7 February 2011.</ref> and made 5 more appearances during the [[2006<U+2013>07 Liga de Honra|2006<U+2013>07 season]] as Penafiel finished 8th in the table. Having reached the end of his contract with the club, Mendes returned to Aves ahead of the [[2007<U+2013>08 Liga de Honra|new season]].<ref name="Futebol365"/>

He made his league debut on 18 August 2007 in a 2<U+2013>1 defeat at home to [[S.C. Olhanense|Olhanense]].<ref>[http://www.lpfp.pt/liga_orangina/pages/jogo.aspx?epoca=20072008&jornada=1&jogo=4875 "Aves 1<U+2013>2 Olhanense"] (in Portuguese). [[Portuguese League for Professional Football]]. Retrieved 7 February 2011.</ref> Mendes scored his first goal in his second stint for Aves on 17 February 2008 in a 1<U+2013>1 draw with [[C.D. Trofense|Trofense]],<ref>[http://www.lpfp.pt/liga_orangina/pages/jogo.aspx?epoca=20072008&jornada=19&jogo=5021 "Aves 1<U+2013>1 Trofense"] (in Portuguese). [[Portuguese League for Professional Football]]. Retrieved 7 February 2011.</ref> and he scored again one week later in a 2<U+2013>1 defeat at [[Varzim S.C.|Varzim]].<ref>[http://www.lpfp.pt/liga_orangina/pages/jogo.aspx?epoca=20072008&jornada=20&jogo=5029 "Varzim 2<U+2013>1 Aves"] (in Portuguese). [[Portuguese League for Professional Football]]. Retrieved 7 February 2011.</ref> He finished the 2007<U+2013>08 season with 23 league appearances and two goals, helping the club finish 8th in the Liga de Honra table.<ref>[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesp/port08.html "Portugal 2007/08"]. [[Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation]]. Jorge Santos, Jan Schoenmakers and Karel Stokkermans. 12 September 2008. Retrieved 22 March 2011.</ref> He made four more league appearances [[2008<U+2013>09 Liga de Honra|the following season]],{{ref label|Aves|E|}} before being released from his contract in January 2009 due to a lack of first team opportunities.<ref name="Aves/Moreirense">[http://www.guimaraesdigital.com/index.php?a=noticias&id=37674 "Nuno Mendes de regresso ao Moreirense"] (in Portuguese). ''O Com<U+00E9>rcio de Guimar<U+00E3>es''. 17 January 2009. Retrieved 7 February 2011.</ref> Mendes dropped down to the [[Portuguese Second Division|third division]] of Portuguese football later that month, for the first time in his career, to return to Moreirense.<ref name="Aves/Moreirense"/> He made his debut on 25 January 2009 in a 1<U+2013>0 win at Chaves,<ref>[http://www.foradejogo.net/match.php?match=200915403511803 "D. Chaves 0<U+2013>1 Moreirense"]. ForaDeJogo. Retrieved 7 February 2011.</ref> and scored his first goal a week later in a 2<U+2013>2 draw with [[F.C. Tirsense|Tirsense]].<ref>[http://www.foradejogo.net/match.php?match=200915403511904 "Moreirense 2<U+2013>2 Tirsense"]. ForaDeJogo. Retrieved 7 February 2011.</ref> Mendes scored two goals in a 3<U+2013>0 win against [[G.D. Ribeir<U+00E3>o|Ribeir<U+00E3>o]] on 8 February 2009 and was sent off later in the game.<ref>[http://www.foradejogo.net/match.php?match=200915403512004 "Ribeir<U+00E3>o 0<U+2013>3 Moreirense"]. ForaDeJogo. Retrieved 7 February 2011.</ref> He scored four goals in 12 appearances for the club, but Moreirense were unable to gain promotion back to Liga de Honra, finishing 2nd, three points behind Chaves.<ref>[http://www.foradejogo.net/team.php?team=9&ano=2009&escalao=0&red=N "Moreirense Futebol Clube: 2008/09 season"]. ForaDeJogo. Retrieved 7 February 2011.</ref>

In August 2009, Mendes joined Liga de Honra club Trofense on a one-year contract.<ref>[http://www.record.xl.pt/arquivo/interior.aspx?content_id=406939 "Nuno Mendes quer ajudar <U+00E0> subida"] (in Portuguese). ''[[Record (newspaper)|Record]]''. 11 August 2009. Retrieved 7 February 2011.</ref><ref>[http://www.guimaraesdigital.com/index.php?a=noticias&id=38878 "Nuno Mendes deixa Moreirense e refor<U+00E7>a Trofense"] (in Portuguese). ''O Com<U+00E9>rcio de Guimar<U+00E3>es''. 10 August 2009. Retrieved 22 March 2011.</ref> He made his league debut on 19 September 2009 in a 3<U+2013>0 defeat at Feirense.<ref>[http://www.lpfp.pt/liga_orangina/pages/jogo.aspx?epoca=20092010&jornada=4&jogo=5962 "Feirense 3<U+2013>0 Trofense"] (in Portuguese). [[Portuguese League for Professional Football]]. Retrieved 7 February 2011.</ref> He made eight more league appearances,<ref name="Futebol365"/> before being released from his contract in January 2010. He then returned to the Segunda Divis<U+00E3>o with [[Gondomar S.C.|Gondomar]] and he made his debut on 31 January 2010 in a 2<U+2013>0 win against [[Vieira S.C.|Vieira]].<ref>[http://www.foradejogo.net/match.php?match=201015400321708 "Gondomar 2<U+2013>0 Vieira"]. ForaDeJogo. Retrieved 7 February 2011.</ref> His first goal for the club came one week later in a 4<U+2013>4 draw with [[S.C. Espinho|Espinho]].<ref>[http://www.foradejogo.net/match.php?match=201015400321808 "Gondomar 4<U+2013>4 Espinho"]. ForaDeJogo. Retrieved 7 February 2011.</ref> Mendes scored his second goal in a 2<U+2013>1 win against [[Padroense F.C.|Padroense]].<ref>[http://www.foradejogo.net/match.php?match=201015400322704 "Padroense 1<U+2013>2 Gondomar"]. ForaDeJogo. Retrieved 13 February 2011.</ref> He made 12 league appearances in the 2009<U+2013>10 season, scoring twice, as they finished 4th in the table.<ref>[http://www.abola.pt/nacional/2divisao.aspx?id=664&op=classificacoes "II - Zona Norte - 2009/2010 Classifica<U+00E7><U+00E3>o"]. ''[[A Bola]]''. Retrieved 22 March 2011.</ref>

==International career==
Mendes represented the Portuguese national team at every youth level, from [[Portugal national under-16 football team|under-16]] to [[Portugal national under-21 football team|under-21]].<ref name="Portugal caps">[http://www.greensonscreen.co.uk/sv-diary.asp?archive=jul05 "The Daily Diary: July 2005"]. Greens on Screen. Retrieved 7 February 2011.</ref> He earned four [[Cap (sport)|caps]] at under-21 level.<ref name="FDJ profile">[http://www.foradejogo.net/player.php?player=197804070001&language=2 "Nuno Mendes"]. ForaDeJogo. Retrieved 7 February 2011.</ref>

==Honours==
;[[RC Strasbourg|Strasbourg]]
*[[Coupe de France]] (1): [[2001 Coupe de France Final|2000<U+2013>01]]

