==Footnotes==
<div style="font-size:95%">
:A. {{note|Felgueiras}}: According to [[L'<U+00C9>quipe]], he scored two goals for Felgueiras in the 1998<U+2013>99 season.<ref name="L'<U+00C9>quipe"/> Futebol365 give him one.<ref name="Futebol365"/>
:B. {{note|LFP}}: Mendes has two profiles on the [[Ligue de Football Professionnel]] website, one for his Strasbourg career in Division 1,<ref name="LFP Strasbourg">[http://www.ligue1.com/joueur/pereira-mendes-nuno "Nuno Pereira Mendes"]. [[Ligue de Football Professionnel]]. Retrieved 7 February 2011.</ref> and one for his career with Cr<U+00E9>teil in Ligue 2.<ref name="LFP Cr<U+00E9>teil">[http://www.ligue1.com/joueur/mendes-nuno "Nuno Mendes"]. [[Ligue de Football Professionnel]]. Retrieved 7 February 2011.</ref> The former says six appearances instead of seven because his latter profile was used in the match with [[SC Bastia|Bastia]].<ref>[http://www.ligue1.com/ligue1/feuille_match/46065 "SC Bastia 3<U+2013>1 RC Strasbourg"]. [[Ligue de Football Professionnel]]. Retrieved 7 February 2011.</ref>
:C. {{note|Braga}}: His profile on ForaDeJogo says he scored three goals in three appearances for Braga, but only list two matches in detail, against Belenenses and Vit<U+00F3>ria Guimar<U+00E3>es.<ref name="FDJ profile"/> Two matches is consistent with L'<U+00C9>quipe,<ref name="L'<U+00C9>quipe"/> and ZeroZeroFootball,<ref name="ZeroZero"/> who both state that Mendes appeared in matches against those two clubs.
:D. {{note|Santa Clara}}: The [[Portuguese League for Professional Football]] website lists Mendes as having played 16 league matches in the 2004<U+2013>05 season,<ref name="LPFP 2004<U+2013>2005"/> but left his name out of the [[starting line-up]] for the game against [[Leix<U+00F5>es S.C.|Leix<U+00F5>es]], leaving them with ten players in the team instead of eleven.<ref>[http://www.lpfp.pt/liga_orangina/pages/jogo.aspx?epoca=20042005&jornada=30&jogo=576 "Sta. Clara 1<U+2013>0 Leix<U+00F5>es"] (in Portuguese). [[Portuguese League for Professional Football]]. Retrieved 7 February 2011.</ref>
:E. {{note|Aves}}: ForaDeJogo and the Portuguese League for Professional Football disagree on who came on as a substitute in the match against [[S.C. Covilh<U+00E3>|Sporting Covilh<U+00E3>]]. ForaDeJogo says that Mendes played in the match, meaning he played in 5 league matches for Aves in the 2008<U+2013>09 season.<ref>[http://www.foradejogo.net/match.php?match=200915400110106 "D. Aves 2<U+2013>0 Sp. Covilh<U+00E3>"]. ForaDeJogo. Retrieved 9 February 2011.</ref> However, the Portuguese League for Professional Football does not.<ref>[http://www.lpfp.pt/liga_orangina/pages/jogo.aspx?epoca=20082009&jornada=1&jogo=5401 "Aves 2<U+2013>0 Covilh<U+00E3>"] (in Portuguese). [[Portuguese League for Professional Football]]. Retrieved 9 February 2011.</ref>
</div>

